Heat 2 tbsp @olive oil{2%tbsp} in a #large saucepan{}, then gently cook 2 finely chopped @onions{2} for ~{5%mins}, until soft but not coloured.

Add 1kg @pumpkin or squash (try kabocha){1%kg}, peeled, deseeded and chopped into chunks, to the pan, then carry on cooking for ~{8-10%mins}, stirring occasionally until it starts to soften and turn golden.

Pour 700ml @vegetable stock or chicken stock{700%ml} into the pan and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Bring to the boil, then simmer for ~{10%mins} until the squash is very soft.

Pour 150ml @double cream{150%ml} into the pan, bring back to the boil, then pur√©e with a #hand blender{}. For an extra-velvety consistency you can pour the soup through a fine sieve. The soup can now be frozen for up to 2 months.

To make the croutons: cut 4 slices @wholemeal seeded bread{4%slices} into small squares. Heat 2 tbsp @olive oil{2%tbsp} in a #frying pan{}, then fry the bread until it starts to become crisp. Add a @handful pumpkin seeds{} to the pan, then cook for a few mins more until they are toasted. These can be made a day ahead and stored in an airtight container.

Reheat the soup if needed, taste for seasoning, then serve scattered with croutons and seeds and drizzled with more olive oil, if you want.
